s)}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Articles and topics related to Andy Murray\n|state=collapsed\n|list1=\n{{Tennis World Number Ones (men)}}\n{{Top ten British male doubles tennis players}}\n{{Footer Olympic Champions Tennis Men}}\n{{Wimbledon men's singles champions}}\n{{Year-End Championships winners}}\n{{US Open men's singles champions}}\n{{US Open boys' singles champions}}\n{{ATP Masters Series tournament winners}}\n{{BBC Sports Personality of the Year winners}}\n{{Laureus World Breakthrough of the Year}}\n{{Tennis in Scotland}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n<!-- HawkEyeBot last run at 14:50:09 (UTC) on 23 October 2012 -->\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Murray, Andy}}\n[[Category:Andy Murray| ]]\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:BBC Sports Personality of the Year winners]]\n[[Category:Clan Murray]]\n[[Category:Grand Slam (tennis) champions in men's singles]]\n[[Category:Hopman Cup competitors]]\n[[Category:Laureus World Sports Awards winners]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male feminists]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Officers of the Order of the British Empire]]\n[[Category:Olympic gold medallists for Great Britain]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in tennis]]\n[[Category:Olympic silver medallists for Great Britain]]\n[[Category:Olympic tennis players of Great Britain]]\n[[Category:Scottish expatriates in Spain]]\n[[Category:Scottish feminists]]\n[[Category:Scottish male tennis players]]\n[[Category:Scottish Olympic medallists]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Glasgow]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Dunblane]]\n[[Category:People in sports awarded knighthoods]]\n[[Category:Tennis players at the 2008 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Tennis players at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Tennis players at the 2016 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:US Open (tennis) champions]]\n[[Category:US Open (tennis) junior champions]]\n[[Category:Wimbledon champions]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2016 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:World No. 1 tennis players]