 July 2012|accessdate=9 July 2012|quote=The only other man in the Open era to lose his first four major finals is Ivan Lendl&nbsp;...}}</ref>||[[Ivan Lendl]]\n|-\n|2010 Australian Open \u2014<br /> 2016 Australian Open||5 runner-up finishes at a single Grand Slam<ref>{{cite news|title=Novak Djokovic beats Andy Murray to win sixth Australian Open title|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/tennis/35453531|work=[[BBC Sport]]|date=31 January 2016|quote=[Murray] becomes only the second man \u2013 behind his former coach Ivan Lendl at the US Open \u2013 to lose five finals at the same Grand Slam since the open era began in 1968.}}</ref>||Ivan Lendl<br />[[Novak Djokovic]]\n|-\n|2008 US Open \u2014<br /> 2016 French Open||Runner-up finishes at all four majors||[[Roger Federer]]<br />Ivan Lendl\n|-\n|'''2012 US Open \u2014<br /> 2013 Australian Open'''||'''Reached final of next consecutive major after winning first title<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tennis-x.com/xblog/2013-01-26/11457.php|title=Australian Open Men's Final Open Thread: Novak Djokovic v Andy Murray|website=tennis-x.com|accessdate=26 January 2013}}</ref>'''|| '''Stands alone'''\n|-\n|'''2012 Olympics \u2014<br /> 2012 US Open'''||'''Winner of Olympic singles gold medal and US Open in same calendar year<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/9535073/Andy-Murrays-US-Open-victory-hailed-as-perfect-end-to-perfect-summer-of-sport.html|title=Andy Murray's US Open victory hailed as perfect end to perfect summer of sport|last=Alleyne|first=Richard|newspaper=The Telegraph|date=11 September 2012|accessdate=3 January 2013|location=London}}</ref>'''||'''Stands alone'''\n|-\n|}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable collapsible collapsed\"\n|-\n!Grand Slam tournaments\n!Time Span\n!Records at each Grand Slam tournament\n!Players matched\n|-\n|'''Australian Open'''||'''2010\u20132016'''||'''[[List of Australian Open men's singles champions|5 runner-up finishes overall]]'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.atpworldtour.com/N