ing historic Olympic tennis gold|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/aug/15/no-respite-for-drained-andy-murray-after-claiming-historic-olympic-tennis-gold|newspaper=The Guardian|publisher=The Guardian London|accessdate=15 August 2016}}</ref>'''||rowspan=2|'''Stands alone'''\n|-\n|'''2012\u20132016'''||'''2 Olympic singles gold medals overall'''\n|-\n|2012\u20132016||3 medals overall (singles, doubles & mixed)||[[Fernando Gonz\u00e1lez]]<br />[[Mike Bryan]]\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\"|Davis Cup\n|-\n|2015||Maximum 8 singles rubber wins in a Davis Cup season<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/tennis/34957711 |title=Andy Murray wins the Davis Cup for Great Britain |work=BBC Sport |publisher= |first=Piers |last=Newbery |date=29 November 2015 |accessdate=29 November 2015}}</ref>||[[John McEnroe]]<br />[[Mats Wilander]]\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\"|Shanghai Masters\n|-\n|2010\u20132016||4 finals ||rowspan=2|[[Novak Djokovic]]\n|-\n|2010\u20132011||2 consecutive titles\n|-\n|'''2010\u20132012'''||'''3 consecutive finals'''||'''Stands alone'''\n|}\n\n===Professional awards===\n* [[ITF World Champions|ITF World Champion]]: 2016.\n* [[ATP Awards|ATP Player of the Year]]: 2016.\n\n== Awards and honours ==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* [[BBC Young Sports Personality of the Year]]: 2004\n* [[BBC Sports Personality Team of the Year Award|BBC Sports Personality Team of the Year]]: 2012, 2015\n* Most Titles in an [[ATP World Tour]] Season: 6 in [[2009 ATP World Tour|2009]], 9 in [[2016 ATP World Tour|2016]]\n* [[US Open Series]] Champion: [[2010 US Open Series|2010]], [[2015 US Open Series|2015]]\n* Best ATP World Tour Match of the Year (3): 2010,{{refn|[[2010 ATP World Tour Finals \u2013 Singles|ATP World Tour Finals]] semi-final lost. Rafael Nadal 6\u20137(5), 6\u20133, 6\u20137(6)<ref>{{cite web|publisher=atpworldtour.com|title=2010 Best Matches of the Year|url=https://www.atpworldtour.com/News/Tennis/2010/12/Other/Best-Matches-Of-The-Year.aspx|date=7 December 2010|accessdat